<li id="cite_note-107"><b><a href="#cite_ref-107" title="">^</a></b> Fiennes, 416–17</li>
<li id="cite_note-108"><b><a href="#cite_ref-108" title="">^</a></b> Solomon, p. xvii</li>
<li id="cite_note-109"><b><a href="#cite_ref-109" title="">^</a></b> <cite class="episode" style="font-style:normal">"Part 6". <i>Blizzard: Race to the Pole</i>. 2006-08-23. No. 6, season 1.</cite></li>
<li id="cite_note-110"><b><a href="#cite_ref-110" title="">^</a></b> The list has numerous anomalies, e.g. actor <a href="/wiki/Michael_Crawford" title="Michael Crawford">Michael Crawford</a> in 17th place ahead of <a href="/wiki/Queen_Victoria" title="Queen Victoria" class="mw-redirect">Queen Victoria</a>, <a href="/wiki/Henry_VIII" title="Henry VIII" class="mw-redirect">Henry VIII</a> and <a href="/wiki/William_Wilberforce" title="William Wilberforce">William Wilberforce</a>. Other explorers listed are <a href="/wiki/Captain_Cook" title="Captain Cook" class="mw-redirect">Captain Cook</a> (12th), <a href="/wiki/Francis_Drake" title="Francis Drake">Francis Drake</a> (49th), <a href="/wiki/Walter_Raleigh" title="Walter Raleigh">Walter Raleigh</a> (91st) and <a href="/wiki/David_Livingstone" title="David Livingstone">David Livingstone</a> (96th).</li>
<li id="cite_note-Max_Jones_289-111">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Max_Jones_289_111-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Max_Jones_289_111-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> Max Jones, p. 289</li>
<li id="cite_note-112"><b><a href="#cite_ref-112" title="">^</a></b> Max Jones, p. 293</li>
</ol>
</div>
